p.-text
  | Date pickers are used for inputting dates from the user. They might be toggled when the user focuses
  | an input of type date in a form.

h2 Examples
p.-text
  | Here are some examples of calendars not attached to any element.

ul#a-tabs--dp.a-tabs
  li.-active
    a(href='#a-tabs--dp-base') Base
  li
    a(href='#a-tabs--dp-active') Active
  li
    a(href='#a-tabs--dp-min-max') Min & max
#a-tabs--dp-base.a-tabs-panel.-active
  .example.-mb--3(style='overflow:hidden;')
    .-p--3
      chi-date
    :code(lang="html")
      <chi-date></chi-date>
#a-tabs--dp-active.a-tabs-panel
  .example.-mb--3(style='overflow:hidden;')
    .-p--3
      chi-date(value="05/15/2019")
    :code(lang="html")
      <chi-date value="05/15/2019"></chi-date>
#a-tabs--dp-min-max.a-tabs-panel
  .example.-mb--3(style='overflow:hidden;')
    .-p--3
      chi-date(min="06/06/2019", max="06/22/2019")
    :code(lang="html")
      <chi-date min="06/06/2019" max="06/22/2019"></chi-date>

h2 Input field
p.-text
  | Use <code>chi-date-picker</code> for including a date-picker input.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    div(style="max-width: 14rem;")
      chi-label(for='date') Date
      chi-date-picker(id="date")
  :code(lang="html",style="height:20rem")
    <chi-label for="date">Date</chi-label>
    <chi-date-picker id="date"></chi-date-picker>

h3 Disabled
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    div(style="max-width: 14rem;")
      chi-label(for='date-disabled') Date
      chi-date-picker(disabled, id="date-disabled")
  :code(lang="html",style="height:20rem")
    <chi-label for="date-disabled">Date</chi-label>
    <chi-date-picker id="date-disabled" disabled></chi-date-picker>

h3 Value, min and max options
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    div(style="max-width: 14rem;")
      chi-label(for='date-min-max') Date
      chi-date-picker(id="date-min-max", value="01/24/2019", min="01/14/2019", max="02/07/2019")
  :code(lang="html",style="height:20rem")
    <chi-label for="date-min-max">Date</chi-label>
    <chi-date-picker id="date-min-max" value="01/24/2019" min="01/14/2019" max="02/07/2019">

